Civil War In Ecuador: A Preview Of Civil War In America. Questions & Answers On The Pale Horse & 4th Seal

1. Which one of the four beasts announced the opening of the fourth seal, based on the context?
A. Man
B. Eagle
C. Lion
D. Calf

2. What was one of the things that the Hebrews did not encounter in Egypt when God delivered them on eagles’ wings?
A. They were persecuted
B. They could not rest
C. They could not work
D. They could not worship

3. According to the book of Revelation, how long did God’s people encounter persecution when Jesus delivered them on eagle’s wings?
A. Mene, Mene, Tekel, Upharsin
B. Time, Times, 1/2 of Time
C. 40 Years
D. 120 Years

4. Time, Times and 1/2 of Time cover how many years?
A. 40 Years
B. 120 Years
C. 1260 Years
D. 2520 Years

5. Which power persecuted God’s people for Time, Times, 1/2 of Time?
A. Pharaoh
B. Popery
C. Nebuchadnezzar
D. Emperor Nero

6. What time period is represented by Time, Times and 1/2 of Time?
A. 508 to 1798
B. 538 to 1798
C. 508 to 1843
D. 538 to 1844

7. What year was the opening of the fourth seal?
A. 321
B. 457
C. 538
D. 508

8. The name of the rider is death and hell followed him. The wages of sin is death. Which power is called the man of sin?
A. Apostate Protestantism
B. Pagan Rome
C. Apostate Christianity
D. Papal Rome

9. What was the transition from the Red Horse to the Black Horse To The Pale Horse?
A. From the Sword To Darkness to the Sword 
B. From the Sword To Money to the Sword
C. From the Sword To the Tail to the Sword
D. From the Sword To Hunger to the Sword

10. Since the pale horse represents the church, what does the color pale represent?
A. Decrease of blood in the body
B. Malnourishment
C. Fear of trouble & death
D. Sickness & Feebleness in the body
